# stack-go-router — go_router 14+

## What it is

Declarative routing for Flutter, deep-link friendly.

## When I choose it

Always, for multi-screen apps.

## When I avoid it

Tiny apps (use Navigator 2 directly only when go_router can't express the flow — rare).

## Conventions I follow

- Typed routes via codegen.
- Single GoRouter in lib/app/router/app_router.dart.
- Auth redirect logic in router redirect callback, NOT in screen build methods.

## Common gotchas

- ShellRoute + statefulShellRoute confusion — pick one based on whether tabs preserve state.
- Hot reload sometimes loses location — restart.

